Liverpool supporters will stage a protest on Tuesday night against Brendan Rodgers ' side against the mounting costs of tickets in the Barclays Premier League .
The die-hard contingent of fans are staying away from The KC Stadium after Hull City charged Liverpool fans £ 50 for their sets .
Last season , the same seats were sold for £ 35 .
Liverpool fans were charged £ 16 for tickets when they went to Hull in August and Evertonians were charge £ 35 for seats at Hull Stadium .
Liverpool manager Brendan Rodgers says he felt sorry for football fans .